Actually, success can be a mixed blessing. Our guild has grown into what I persoanlly consider to be a very nice balance of RP and uberness. We formed an alliance of 6 other smaller guilds called the Union of Heroes.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub128.ezboard.com/bunionofheroes">pub128.ezboard.com/bunionofheroes</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
I see that there is a similar alliance here. So far, it's worked out very well for us.<br>
<br>
So I'm happy to give advice. I would offer this: Decide exactly what your goal for your guild is. Is it a certain number of members? A Storyline that ends in a glorious battle?<br>
<br>
If you know where you want to take this guild, it will be easier to decide who should be along for the ride.<br>
<br>
Now, It's almost too quiet here. I'd like to perhaps join a guild here that isn't too much like the Crusade. Any advice can be sent to joooly2000@yahoo.com <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:green;font-family:lucida handwriting;">Lady Regent Hollihawk Sugarpine</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
